# Gitflow

Follow [gitflow](https://nvie.com/posts/a-successful-git-branching-model/) for all changes.

## Branches
- **main** — production-ready; protected; merge only via PR
- **develop** — integration branch for ongoing work (create when needed)
- **feature/** — new work (`feature/123-short-description`)
- **release/** — release prep (`release/1.2.0`)
- **hotfix/** — urgent production fixes (`hotfix/critical-bug`)

## Rules
1. Never commit directly to **main** or **develop** — use a branch and PR
2. Branch from **develop** (or **main** for hotfixes)
3. Keep PRs focused; one concern per branch where practical
4. Use clear commit messages; PR title summarizes the change
5. Do not push secrets; use user secrets, GitHub secrets, or env vars

## Agent workflow
- Before git work: confirm target branch and base branch
- Create/switch to an appropriately named branch before edits
- Summarize impacted apps in PR description (`apps/dert-api`, etc.)
